name: U-Haul Moving & Storage of Spring
directions:
there's 2 bathrooms, one is in the front - drive into the parking lot and go to the side that says "custom hitches + boxes", in through the sliding door, walk past the boxes, bathroom is in the back right corner. 
the 2nd bathroom is in storage - go in through the sliding double doors under the "climate controlled self storage" sign, 
walk past the reuse center and turn right, walk forward until you pass through the black double doors, turn right again, and bathroom is at the end of the windowed hallway.
comment: If you go to the storage bathroom, there's no climate control, but no one will question you or talk to you.

name: Hesburger
directions:
Directly to the right of the registers. Might have to ask to unlock so it's better to ask if it's open.
The sink is big and low, enough to was up a baby if it's necessary. I should however warn that the sink is prone to splasing over the edge so I recommend only turning the faucet to a small stream to avoid accidents.
No stalls, one wheelchair friendly toilet and a sink.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer, just be mindful that other people also would need to use the bathroom.

Small room with low ceiling and a short door with frosted glass. Lightswitch is on the outside by the door. Just one toilet and a small sink with a mirror.
You don't have to pay or ask for key but it's a general courtesy to not take too long especially if it's clearly busy hour.
Too small for a wheelchair.
